sgrep '"expression"' filename                   Display region expression hits, without intervening newlines
sgrep -o%r\\n '"expression"' filename           Display region expression hits, following each region with a newline
                                                This is grep-ish behaviour

sgrep '"{".."}" not containing "fred"' filename       All {..} blocks not referring to fred
sgrep '("/*".."*/") containing "fred"' *.c            All C style comments containing fred
